!***********************************************************************

Description:
------------
plasRedChem is a dimensionality-reduction library for plasma
chemical kinetics. Reduction is performed using the Directed Relation
Graphs with Error Propagation (DRGEP) method [1,2]. 

Author: Z. Nikolaou 

References: 
 [1] P. Pepiot Desjardins, H. Pitsch. Combust. Flame 154 (2008) 67-81. 
 [2] T. Lu, C.K. Law. Proc. Combust. Inst. 30 (2005) 1333-1341. 

User inputs:
------------ 
 1. A detailed chemical mechanism in ZDPlasKin format e.g. kinet.inp,
    kinet.txt etc.  
 2. Individual reaction rate data in binary Fortran format obtained 
    using the provided WRITE_BIN subroutine under ./utils/. 
 3. A control file for the reduction as in the examples directory.  

To use: 
-------

1. Set environment variables: 
   
   source setenv.sh. 

2. make clean, then make redChem. 

!***********************************************************************
